.Dd April 19, 2026
.Dt MPORT.MERGE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm mport.merge
.Nd merge multiple package bundle files into one output bundle
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar chroot-path
.Fl o Ar output-file
.Ar pkgfile ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
merges multiple input package bundle files into a single output bundle.
This is primarily a packaging helper.
.Bl -tag -width ".Fl o Ar output-file"
.It Fl c Ar chroot-path
Run inside the specified chroot.
.It Fl o Ar output-file
Write the merged bundle to
.Ar output-file .
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Merge two package files into one output bundle:
.Dl $ mport.merge -o combined.mport part1.mport part2.mport
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr mport 1 ,
.Xr mport.create 1
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility appeared in
.Mx 0.3 .
